cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.AR, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing parallel execution of unstructured-mesh algorithms on GPUs.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses numerical algorithms such as finite volume and finite element algorithms.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of numerical algorithms on GPUs.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper specifically targets modern many-core architectures such as GPUs.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper presents a new software library for implementing the optimized algorithms.
